An APC gubernatorial aspirant in Kogi State, Prince Mustapha Mona Audu, has said that he is currently the only candidate capable of beating Governor Yahaya Bello in the November 16 governorship election in the state. A statement issued, yesterday, indicated that Audu said this during a charity outreach programme of providing accessible clean water in Idu, Koton Karfe, after his tour of the 21 local government areas of the state. He assured the people that he had what it took to provide infrastructure across the state if he emerged governor. Similarly, his wife Zahra Audu, had provided delivery kits to 200 women, and assured that they were collaborating with Women Africa to empower 4000 women in the state. page 10 replace page 7 add Auduâ€™s death a big loss-Masari Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin